<L>__{interior privy chamber, whitehall palace day}
<A>__{an agitated group is gathered in this room where the business of state is transacted. we catch glimpses of the queen in their midst, preparing to leave, as her ministers try to persuade her of the seriousness of the situation: sir christopher hatton, 30s, an ambitious courtier; lord howard, 50s, a weathered old campaigner; and standing back from the rest, watching from the side lines, sir francis walsingham, the queen's veteran friend and adviser.}
<C>__{hatton}
<D>__{be warned by the atrocities in france! god fearing christians murdered by papist cut throats inflamed by hatred of the truth!}
<C>__{howard}
<D>__{we know the catholics take their orders from spain. the spanish speak openly of mary stuart as queen of england in waiting.}
<C>__{elizabeth}
<P>__{(sharply)}
<D>__{mary stuart is a queen cast out by her own ungrateful nation.}
